accessibility.text: The researcher’s own social origins and coordinates (class/gender/race) – not projecting own values and beliefs on to a different social world.
The researcher’s position in the academic field – using ‘accepted’ methodologies, taking approaches that will make them professionally competitive

The ‘intellectualist bias’ which views everything as signifiying something to be studied. Maxwell suggests that this is behind the ‘curse of fandom’, where theory is wrongly applied to a practice because the researcher wants it to be viewed in a particular way.
